data.name: label_cohrency_info.Text
data.value: Coherency matrix is a 2 by 2 Hermitian matrix which contains information about polarization state and degree of polarization of a single wavelength coherent light. Diagonal elements represent the intensity of x and y components while off diagonal ones show the state of polarization and how much an arbitrary light is polarized. Gxx and Gxy are real numbers and Gxy is a complex number. While assigning values, consider the unequality |Gxx||Gyy| >= |Gxy|^2
